data.title: These are the most famous University of Michigan alumni in school history
data.meta_description: Established in 1817 in Detroit and moving to Ann Arbor in 1837, this is the oldest university in Michigan.
data.text:
Story by Edward Pevos of MLive - epevos@MLive.com

Photo by Junfu Han | The Ann Arbor News

Established in 1817 in Detroit and moving to Ann Arbor in 1837, this is the oldest university in Michigan. Here are the most famous alumni from U of M ahead their bowl game against Florida State on December 30, 2016.

James Earl Jones

Photo from the Grand Rapids Press

Born in Mississippi, the 85 year old actor graduated from the University of Michigan in 1955.

Lucy Liu

Born in Queens, NY, the 47 year old actress transferred to the University of Michigan from from New York University in the late 80s. Liu was a member of the Chi Omega sorority. She earned a bachelor's degree in Asian languages and cultures and worked as a waitress at the Ann Arbor Comedy Showcase.

Larry Page

Photo by Lon Horwedel - The Ann Arbor News

Born in East Lansing, Larry Page co-founded Google in 1998. The 43 year old holds a Bachelor of Science in computer engineering from the University of Michigan.

Ann B. Davis

Born in 1926 in New York, the actress known for playing Alice on "The Brady Bunch" graduated from the University of Michigan in 1948. She died at age 88 in 2014.

Ann Coulter

Photo by Jamie Charbeneau-Pisella

Born in New York City, the 54 year old is a writer, lawyer and controversial political commentator. She graduated from Cornell in 1984 and received her J.D. from the University of Michigan Law School in 1988.

Tony Fadell

There probably wouldn't be iPods without the 47 year old inventor. He was the Senior Vice President of the iPod division at Apple in the late 2000s. A graduate of Grosse Point South High School, Fadell graduated from the University of Michigan in 1991.

David Alan Grier

Photo courtesy of WDIV

The 60 year old actor and Detroit native graduated high school from Cass Tech and received a B.A. from the University of Michigan. He then went on to graduate from the Yale School of Drama in 1981.

Selma Blair

The 44 year old Southfield, Michigan native and actress graduated from the University of Michigan in 1994.

Gerald R. Ford

Our 38th President was born in Nebraska. He lived in Grand Rapids and attended the University of Michigan in the early 1930s. He played linebacker and long snapper. The team had undefeated seasons and national championships while he played there in 1932 and 1933.

Branch Rickey

The Ohio native (pictured right) was a Major League Baseball executive elected to the Hall of Fame in 1967. He broke the MLB color barrier by signing Jackie Robinson. Rickey attended U of M in 1911. He died in 1965 at the age of 83.

Madonna

AP Photo/Kin Cheung

Born in Bay City, Michigan, the 58 year old singer received a dance scholarship to attend the University of Michigan in the late 70s. She dropped out of college in 1978 to move to New York City and the rest is history.

Arthur Miller

Born in Harlem in 1915, the American playwright attended the University of Michigan in the 1930s. He wrote his first play there called "No Villain." He graduated in 1938. Miller died in 2005 at 89. Among his most popular plays are "All My Sons," "Death of a Salesman," "The Crucible," and "A View from the Bridge." He also wrote several screenplays including "The Misfits."

Darren Criss

The 29 year old San Francisco native is best known for starring on the FOX show "Glee." Criss graduated from the University of Michigan in 2009.

Iggy Pop

Photo by Melanie Maxwell - AnnArbor.com

The 69 year old Muskegon native attended the University of Michigan in 1963 and 1964. He is a member of the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame.

Christine Lahti

Photo by Van Rebin - The WB

The 66 year old Birmingham, Michigan native earned an Oscar nomination for her role in the 1984 movie "Swing Shift." She's an eight-time Golden Globe nominee and a six-time Emmy Award nominee. She received a bachelor's degree in Drama at the University of Michigan.

Dick Costolo

The 52 year old Royal Oak native was the CEO of Twitter from 2010 to 2015. He graduated from the University of Michigan in 1985.

Lin Shaye

The 72 year old Detroit native is known for her roles in many horror movies. She also starred in the comedy movies "Kingpin" and "There's Something About Mary." She attended U of M in the mid 60s.

John Delorean

The Detroit native was known for his work at General Motors and as the founder of the DeLorean Motor Company. DeLorean attended Lawrence Tech, graduated from the Chrysler Institute with a master's degree and took night classes at U of M to earn credits for his MBA degree, which he finished in 1957. He died in 2005 at age 80.

Gilda Radner

AP Photo/Bill Polo

The actress and Detroit native attended the University of Michigan from 1964 to 1970 before dropping out her senior year. She died of cancer in 1989 at age 42.

Derek Jeter

Photo by Hugh Carey - MLive

Born in New Jersey and raised in Kalamazoo, the former Major League baseball all-star and New York Yankee never played baseball for the University of Michigan. The Yankees drafted him number 6 overall in the first round. Jeter did take classes at UM in the fall of 1992 after playing in the minors.

Tom Brady

AP Photo/Steven Senne

Born in California, the New England Patriots quarterback played at the University of Michigan from 1996 to 1999. The four-time Super Bowl MVP was a sixth round draft pick of the Patriots in 2000.

Gavin Creel

The 40 year old Ohio native has received two Tony Award nominations for his work in musical theater. He graduated from the University of Michigan in 1998.

Jack Kevorkian

Photo by Charles V. Tines

Known as "Dr. Death," the Pontiac native graduated from the University of Michigan in 1952. He died in 2011 at age 83.

Claude Shannon

The Petoskey native is known as the "father of information theory." Shannon is also known for founding digital circuit design theory. He graduated from the University of Michigan in 1936 with two degrees. Shannon died in 2001 at age 84.

Rick Snyder

AP Photo/David Eggert

The 58 year old Battle Creek native is currently in his second term as Governor of Michigan. He earned degrees at the University of Michigan in 1977, 1979 and 1982.

Jessye Norman

Born in Georgia, she is a Grammy winning opera singer. Norman earned her degree from the University of Michigan in 1968.

Eric Millegan

The 42 year old New Jersey native is best known for playing Dr. Zack Addy on the FOX series "Bones." He received a Bachelor of Fine Arts degree at the University of Michigan.

Mike Wallace

The Massachusetts native and longtime journalist graduated from the University of Michigan in 1939.

Dr. Ben Carson

AP Photo/Gerald Herbert

The 64 year old Detroit native and retired neurosurgeon graduated from Yale, but attended the University of Michigan in 1977. He's also a former Republican Presidential candidate.

Ted Kaczynski

Known as the "Unabomber," the 74 year old Illinois native earned a PhD in mathematics at the University of Michigan in the 1960s. He earned his undergraduate degree at Harvard.

Scott Steiner

Photo by Melanie Maxwell | MLive.com

The 54 year old Bay City native was a professional wrestler. He attended the University of Michigan where he excelled on the wrestling team for all four years.

Robert Kotick

The 53 year old businessman is the president and CEO of Activision Blizzard known for "Call of Duty," "World of Warcraft" and more. He began his career as a software developer in 1983 while he was at the University of Michigan.

Margo Martindale

Photo by Richard Shotwell/Invision/AP

The 65 year old Texas native and actress won an Emmy Award for her recurring role as Mags Bennett on "Justified." She has been nominated for four Emmy Awards for her role as Claudia on "The Americans." She attended U of M in 1973.

Bob McGrath

The 84 year old Illinois native is best known for playing Bob on "Sesame Street." McGrath is a 1954 graduate of the University of Michigan's School of Music.

Marian Mercer

The Tony Award winning actress from Ohio graduated from the University of Michigan in the late 1950s. She died in 2011 at age 75.

Michael Phelps

AP Photo/Lee Jin-man

The 31 year old Baltimore native is the most decorated Olympian in history with 28 medals. The five time Olympian attended U of M in the mid 2000s.

Michael Patrick O'Brien

The 40 year old Blissfield, Michigan native is an actor, writer, and comedian, best known for his work on "Saturday Night Live." He attended the University of Michigan in the late 90s.

David Paymer

The 62 year old New York native and actor is best known for his work in "Mr. Saturday Night," "Quiz Show," and "City Slickers." He graduated from the University of Michigan in the mid '70s.

Edward H. White

The Texas native became the first American to walk in space in 1965. He received his master's at U of M in 1959. White died at age 36 in 1967 during training for Apollo 1.

David Barger

The 58 year old New Jersey native was the CEO of JetBlue Airways from 2007 to 2015. He attended the University of Michigan in the early 80s.

Rich Eisen

The 47 year old Brooklyn native is a journalist for the NFL Network and CBS Sports. He graduated from U of M in 1990.

Adam Schefter

The 49 year old New York native is a sports writer and sports TV analyst. He graduated from the University of Michigan in 1989.
